| 120k train / 7.6k test | Text classification | datasets/ag_news/ | Transformer baseline experiments |\n| Online News Popularity | UCI | 39,644 rows, 61 cols | Popularity prediction (attention proxy) | datasets/online_news_popularity/ | Internet attention-economy signal |\n\nSee `datasets/README.md` for download and load instructions.\n\n### Code Repositories\nTotal repositories cloned: 3\n\n| Name | URL | Purpose | Location | Notes |\n|------|-----|---------|----------|-------|\n| transformers | https://github.com/huggingface/transformers | Attention-based model definitions and training/inference APIs | code/transformers/ | Broad baseline library |\n| diffusers | https://github.com/huggingface/diffusers | Diffusion pipelines and schedulers | code/diffusers/ | Generative AI experiments |\n| RecBole | https://github.com/RUCAIBox/RecBole | Recommendation benchmark toolkit | code/RecBole/ | Internet ranking/attention metrics |\n\nSee `code/README.md` for notes.\n\n### Resource Gathering Notes\n\n#### Search Strategy\n1. Ran `paper-finder` first (as required) with fast/diligent attempts.\n2. Because returned results were weakly relevant for this specific hypothesis, used curated canonical arXiv retrieval.\n3. Prioritized papers linking: attention math -> generative AI systems -> internet recommendation/CTR behavior.\n\n#### Selection Criteria\n- Open-access PDFs\n- Strong methodological grounding\n- Widely used baselines and metrics\n- Direct relevance to hypothesis claims\n\n#### Challenges Encountered\n- `paper-finder` returned mostly low-relevance items for this query.\n- Missing shell utilities (`wget`, `unzip`) required fallback to `curl` and Python extraction.\n\n#### Gaps and Workarounds\n- Direct peer-reviewed \"attention economy\" economics papers often behind paywalls; workaround was to include recommender/CTR literature that operationalizes user attention behavior.\n\n### Recommendations for Experiment Design\n1. **Primary dataset(s)**: Use `Online News Popularity` as main internet-attention proxy; use `AG News` for controlled transformer-attention ablations.\n2. **Baseline methods**: Compare linear/MLP/RNN baselines against transformer/self-attention and DIN-style attention models.\n3. **Evaluation metrics**: Classification F1/accuracy plus ranking/engagement metrics (`NDCG`, `HR`, `AUC`) and regression error for popularity prediction.\n4. **Code to adapt/reuse**: `transformers` for attention variants, `RecBole` for recommendation evaluation protocols, `diffusers` for generative-attention case studies.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
